text:
Spaichingen is a town of the district of Tuttlingen in the state of Baden-Württemberg, Germany. As of 31 December 2018, it has about 13,000 people lived there.
Geography.
Spaichingen lies on the Prim at the foot of the Dreifaltigkeitsberg (Holy Trinity Mountain). It is 11 km northwest of Tuttlingen, and 13 km southeast of Rottweil. It has an elevation of above sea level.
